- HTML provides structure to the content apperaingon a website.
- A markup language is a computer language that defines the structure and presentation of raw text.
- In HTMl a computer can interpret raw text wrapped in HTML elements.
- Hypertext is text displayed on a computer or device that provide access to other text through links, also known as hyperlinks.
- Elements are made up one opening tag <> and one closing </> and the content between it.
- <body> </body> - once a file has body many different types of content including text, images and buttons can be added to the body.
- Parent element - main element.
- Child element - rested inside parent element.
- In HTML here are six different headings.
- <div> is a container that divides the page into sections. Always remember to put two spaces of indentation.
- Attributed are content added to the opening tag of an element and can be used in several ways from providing information 
  to changing styling. Attributes are made up of two parts name and value. <div id = "">.
- If you want to display text in HTML you can use paragrahs or span.paragraphs <p> for block of plain text and span <span>. 
  for short pieces of text or other HTML, used to seperate text.
- If you want to divide content into blocks it is better to use div.
- You can use styling text using HTML tags. The <em> tag emphasizes text, while the <strong> tag highlights important text.
- <em> = italac;  <strong> = bold.
- If you are interested in modifying the spacing in the browser, you can use HTML line break element <br>.
- You can use unordered list <ul> to create a list of items in no particular order. Individual list items must be 
  added to the unordered list using the <li> tag.
- Ordered list <ol> means that list items are numbered.
- <img> tag allow us to to add images, it is a self inclosed tag. It has required attribute src. <img src="  ">.
- alt altrnative text attribte inside <img> tag <img alt="  ">. It is used to give description to something.
- <video> tag allow us to show videos but reqire closing tag </video>. Attributes for <video> are self enclosed in the tag
  header. src attribute is hosted alongside your webpage, width and height attribute are  used to set the size of the video.
  control attributed to add basic controls, must be included.
- Declarative Languages tell interpreter what to do, not how to do it.
- Iterative Language tell interpreter what to do.
- Adavntages of coherent HTML Structure: Readability, Accessibility, Ease of Styling.
- <section> tag when there is a need for symantic information.
- Divitis- excessive misuse of divs to markup a page
